%N A317496 Triangle T(n,k) = T(n-1,k) + 3*T(n-3,k-1) for k = 0..floor(n/3) with T(0,0) = 1, T(n,k) = 0 for n or k < 0, read by rows.
%C A317496 The numbers in rows of the triangle are along a "second layer" of skew diagonals pointing top-right in center-justified triangle given in A013610 ((1+3*x)^n) and  along a "second layer" of skew diagonals pointing top-left in center-justified triangle given in A027465 ((3+x)^n), see links. (Note: First layer of skew diagonals in center-justified triangles of coefficients in expansions of (1+3*x)^n and (3+x)^n are given in A304236 and A304249 respectively.)
%C A317496 The coefficients in the expansion of 1/(1-x-3x^3) are given by the sequence generated by the row sums.
%C A317496 If s(n) is the row sum at n, then the ratio s(n)/s(n-1) is approximately 1.863706527819..., when n approaches infinity.
